# {{PROJECT_NAME}} -- Execution Layer (dev_docs)

> This folder is the **single source of truth** for task management,
> service ownership, and development standards.

---

## Folder Structure

| Folder | Contents | When to Use |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| `./` (root) | STATUS.md, CHANGELOG.md, this README | Check task status, log work |
| `foundations/` | Session playbook, design system, quality gates | Start of every session |
| `tasks/` | Individual task files (one per task) | When working on a specific task |
| `components/` | Component catalog and index | When building or reviewing UI |
| `services/` | Service hub files (one per service) | When working on a service area |
| `audit/` | Audit reports by domain | When assessing code quality |
| `references/` | Doc map, quickstart, risk register, patterns | Quick lookups and onboarding |

---

## How to Find Tasks

1. Open **STATUS.md** -- scan for tasks with Status = "Ready"
2. Open the task file in `tasks/` matching the task ID
3. Read the **Context Header** -- it lists the 6 files to load
4. Follow the **File Plan** table to know exactly what to create/edit

---

## How to Read Service Hubs

Each file in `services/` is the **hub** for one service area.
It contains:
- Backend/frontend implementation status
- Screen inventory with routes
- API endpoint catalog
- Component list
- Business rules and known issues
- Links to detailed specs in `{{SPEC_LAYER_PATH}}`

